The Chinese embassy has donated $66 396 to government following the catastrophe. Chinese President, Xi Jinping, has also expressed his condolences to President Cyril Ramaphosa. This after over 400 people died in the devastating floods. Infrastructure has also been destroyed in several parts of the province. The Chinese ambassador to South Africa is Chen Xiadong says: "We are sudden to know that the recent rainfall and floods has resulted in significant casualties and property loss in KwaZulu-Natal. Our thoughts and prayers are with those people who were affected by the disaster." Full interview click audio below: --ChannelAfrica--